### =============================================================================
### Exercise 7 — HCQL (CQL over HTTP)
###
### Exercises the HCQL protocol adapter on the TravelService.
### Covers CQL text queries (text/plain) and CQN JSON queries (application/json).
###
### How to run:
### 1. Enable HCQL on the service (see exercise Step 1).
### 2. Start the app:  `cds watch`   (defaults to port 4004)
### 3. Open this file in VS Code with the "REST Client" extension installed,
###    then click "Send Request" above each block.
###
### Every request runs under user `alice` (mocked auth).
### =============================================================================

@host    = http://localhost:4004
@hcql    = {{host}}/hcql/travel
@auth    = Basic alice:


### =============================================================================
### 7.3 — Query with CQL text (plain text body)
###   Sends a CQL SELECT as plain text. Returns travels with selected fields.
### =============================================================================

### CQL text — select travels with basic fields
POST {{hcql}}
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: text/plain

SELECT from Travels { ID, Description, BeginDate, EndDate, TotalPrice, Currency.code as Currency }


### =============================================================================
### 7.4 — Query with CQN JSON body
###   Same query as above, but expressed as CQN JSON notation.
###   This format works on both CAP Node.js and CAP Java.
### =============================================================================

### CQN JSON — select travels (cross-runtime format)
POST {{hcql}}
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "SELECT": {
    "from": { "ref": ["Travels"] },
    "columns": [
      { "ref": ["ID"] },
      { "ref": ["Description"] },
      { "ref": ["BeginDate"] },
      { "ref": ["EndDate"] },
      { "ref": ["TotalPrice"] },
      { "ref": ["Currency", "code"], "as": "Currency" }
    ],
    "limit": { "rows": { "val": 5 } }
  }
}


### =============================================================================
### 7.5 — Use expands to query nested data
###   Query travels with their bookings including flight details resolved
###   through associations.
### =============================================================================

### CQL text — travels with nested bookings (expand)
POST {{hcql}}
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: text/plain

SELECT from Travels {
  ID, Description, Status.name as Status,
  Bookings {
    Pos, Flight.date as FlightDate,
    Flight.airline as Airline,
    FlightPrice, Currency.code as Currency
  }
} limit 2


### =============================================================================
### 7.6 — Filtering and ordering
###   Query only open travels, sorted by begin date descending.
### =============================================================================

### CQL text — open travels ordered by BeginDate desc
POST {{hcql}}
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: text/plain

SELECT from Travels {
  ID, Description, BeginDate, TotalPrice
} where Status.code = 'O' order by BeginDate desc limit 5
